    "# <ins>**1 Quadratic Equations**</ins>\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6c8a59ee-216c-4439-ac7c-5a26b30d543e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## **Introduction**\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fbb504a9-4955-4aa2-94dd-04a7ed37d481",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Polynomialdeg2.svg/300px-Polynomialdeg2.svg.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1b9fa694-a0e5-4950-b54a-0524965b4666",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The general form of a quadratic equation is:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "ax^{2} + bx + c = 0\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f3ba84d2-e856-4f6d-9b2f-aec33bb7e452",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## **Solutions**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "58cf17ec-e928-4c70-9129-67ff7c14722b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Provided $a \\ne 0$, we can use an elementary algebraic method called <ins>[completing the square](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Completing_the_square) </ins> to show that a quadratic equation has the following solution:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "005f132b-61fe-45a3-aee3-7271aa58e4b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$\n",
    "x = \\dfrac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}\n",
    "$$\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9b8045b4-d9c4-4dc8-b6bd-f19306d87916",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## **Discriminant**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cff5b4a7-7818-4a89-ae2e-718118d51614",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The quantity $\\Delta = b^{2} - 4ac$ is called **discriminant** of the equation and decides the nature of its solutions. The table below shows the various possibilities."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e9894bc2-a70f-48ce-9c5e-60d535e7cd4a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "|**Discriminant**   |   **Roots**|\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "|$\\Delta = b^{2} - 4ac = 0$ |A single solution of $-b/(2a)$  |\n",
    "|$\\Delta = b^{2} - 4ac \\gt 0$ |Two distinct solutions\n",
    "|$\\Delta = b^{2} - 4ac \\lt 0$|No real solutions; both are complex.|\n"
   ]
  },
